Gonopods (figs. 
37–39
) relatively small; angiocoxites tightly appressed nearly all their length, slightly diverging distally; MAPs distally flared laterally, with small, subtriangular subapical spine, apical spine absent; LAPs large, basally broad, evenly curved, undivided. Colpocoxites much reduced, apically bilobed, fused nearly all their length; median colpocoxite processes absent. Ninth legpair typical of troglobionts, femur and three apical segments fused, coxoprefemur with paired basal knobs, distally swollen.
